A very striking instance of this is to be found even in Chinese--a language which differs fundamentally from all those belonging to the Sanskrit family--it is in the commentary to the Y-King,[280] accurately rendered by Peter Regis as follows: "_Yang, seu materia cÅlestis_, vult _rursus ingredi, vel_ (_ut verbis doctoris Tsching-tse utar_) vult _rursus esse in superiore loco; scilicet illius naturÃ¦ ratio ita fert, seu innata lex_."
